## 4. Sets

A **Set** stores unique values. JavaScript’s standard library provides `Set`, and TypeScript types it naturally.

```ts
const skills = new Set(["boxing", "Muay Thai", "karate", "Muay Thai"]);
console.log(skills);
```

Even though `"Muay Thai"` appears twice in the input, the set only keeps one copy.

Membership checks:

```ts
console.log(skills.has("boxing"));
console.log(skills.has("MMA"));
```

Sets are useful when you care about:

* uniqueness
* fast membership checks

