## Indexing reminder

TypeScript arrays and tuples use **zero-based indexing**, just like JavaScript.

```ts
const colors: string[] = ["red", "blue", "green"];

console.log(colors[0]); // red
console.log(colors[1]); // blue
console.log(colors[2]); // green
```

